Subscription Manager - Deployment Guide
================================================================================

PREREQUISITES
================================================================================
1. .NET 10.0 Desktop Runtime (Windows)
   - Download: https://dotnet.microsoft.com/download/dotnet/10.0
   - Select the x64 or x86 Desktop Runtime depending on your system

2. MySQL Server (version compatible with MySql.Data 9.6.0)
   - Download: https://dev.mysql.com/downloads/mysql/
   - Recommended version: 8.0 or later

3. Gmail Account (for email notifications)
   - Must have 2-Step Verification enabled
   - Must generate an App Password


DEPLOYMENT STEPS
================================================================================

Step 1: Install .NET 10.0 Desktop Runtime
------------------------------------------------
- Download and run the .NET 10.0 Desktop Runtime installer
- Follow the installation wizard
- Restart your computer if prompted


Step 2: Install MySQL Server
------------------------------------------------
- Download and install MySQL Server (8.0 or later recommended)
- During installation, set a root password (remember this!)
- Complete the MySQL Server setup process
- Verify MySQL service is running (check Services.msc)


Step 3: Configure MySQL Database
------------------------------------------------
1. Open MySQL Workbench or a MySQL command-line client
2. Connect as root user
3. Create a database for the Subscription Manager:
   CREATE DATABASE SubscriptionManager;
   
4. Create a dedicated MySQL user (optional but recommended):
   CREATE USER 'subscription_user'@'localhost' IDENTIFIED BY 'your_secure_password';
   GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON SubscriptionManager.* TO 'subscription_user'@'localhost';
   FLUSH PRIVILEGES;
   
5. Create the necessary database tables (the application should handle
   table creation automatically on first run)


Step 4: Configure Email Settings
------------------------------------------------
1. Open EmailSettings.vb file
2. Update the following constants as needed:
   - SMTP_HOST: "smtp.gmail.com" (default)
   - SMTP_PORT: 587 (default)
   - SMTP_EMAIL: Your Gmail address
   - SMTP_PASSWORD: Your Gmail App Password
   - MAILBEE_LICENSE_KEY: Your MailBee.NET license key
   
3. To generate a Gmail App Password:
   - Go to Google Account Settings &gt; Security
   - Enable 2-Step Verification
   - Under "Signing in to Google," select "App Passwords"
   - Create a new App Password (select "Other" and name it "Subscription Manager")
   - Use this generated password in SMTP_PASSWORD


Step 5: Build the Application
------------------------------------------------
Option A: Using Visual Studio
- Open Subscription Manager.sln in Visual Studio
- Select "Release" configuration
- Build the solution (Build &gt; Build Solution)

Option B: Using .NET CLI
- Open Command Prompt or PowerShell
- Navigate to the project directory
- Run: dotnet build --configuration Release


Step 6: Deploy the Application Files
------------------------------------------------
1. Navigate to the Release build output folder:
   bin\Release\net10.0-windows\
   
2. Copy all files and folders from this directory to your deployment target folder
   (e.g., C:\Program Files\Subscription Manager)
   
3. Ensure the deployment folder contains:
   - Subscription Manager.exe
   - All DLL files
   - Runtimes folder
   - Any resource files


Step 7: Configure Application Settings (First Run)
------------------------------------------------
1. Launch Subscription Manager.exe
2. On first run, the application will:
   - Create the necessary database tables
   - Prompt you to configure the database connection
3. Enter your database connection details (if not configured in code):
   - Server: localhost
   - Database: SubscriptionManager
   - Username: your MySQL username
   - Password: your MySQL password


Step 8: Test the Application
------------------------------------------------
1. Launch the application
2. Add a test subscription to verify functionality
3. Test the email notification feature
4. Verify payment tracking works correctly


TROUBLESHOOTING
================================================================================

Issue: .NET Runtime not found
- Ensure .NET 10.0 Desktop Runtime is installed

Issue: MySQL connection error
- Verify MySQL service is running
- Check database name, username, and password
- Ensure the user has appropriate permissions

Issue: Email notifications not sending
- Verify Gmail App Password is correct
- Check that 2-Step Verification is enabled
- Ensure firewall allows outbound connections on port 587
- Check application logs for error details


MAINTENANCE
================================================================================
- Regularly back up the MySQL database
- Keep .NET runtime and MySQL server updated
- Update MailBee.NET license key if it expires
- Change Gmail App Password if compromised


